msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"orientation\n"
": Portrait or landscape (note that darktable chooses the best fit by default).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"units\n"
": The unit to use for setting the margins: “mm”, “cm”, or “inch”.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"margins\n"
": Set each margin separately, or all together by clicking on the middle “lock” button.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"image width/height\n"
": This information field displays the actual image width and height (given with the selected units) on the paper.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"scale factor\n"
": This information field displays the scaling of the image to fit on the paper. If this value is less than 1 the image is down-scaled, otherwise it is up-scaled. This is an important factor to watch -- a value that is too large (up-scale) may result in a low quality print. The corresponding dpi (dots per inch) is also displayed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"alignment\n"
": Select the alignment of the image on the paper.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"profile\n"
": The export profile to use. This profile is the entry point used for the next transformation using the printer's ICC profile. Usually it is better to prefer a large gamut (e.g. AdobeRGB) rather than a smaller one (e.g. sRGB).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"intent\n"
": The rendering intent to use when exporting the image. For more information see [rendering intent](../../../special-topics/color-management/rendering-intent.md).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"style\n"
": Choose a style to apply when exporting the image -- defaults to “none”. See the [export](../shared/export.md) module for a more detailed discussion of applying a style during export.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/print/print-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mode\n"
": Whether the chosen style should be appended to the existing history stack or replace it completely. See the [export](../shared/export.md) module for more details.\n"
msgstr ""

