msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The waveform scope includes spatial data about the image. The y-axis represents the distribution of pixels by lightness for each channel. The x-axis represents the distribution of this data across the x-axis of the image. The lightness of each point of the waveform represents the number of pixels at that position.  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The thick dotted horizontal line at the top of the waveform histogram represents 100% lightness. Any channel displayed above that line may be clipped in the resulting image. The thinner dotted horizontal line represents 50% lightness. The bottom of the scope represents 0% lightness.  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "As with the \"regular\" histogram, it is possible to selectively display red, green, and blue channels, or (the default) all three of them.  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "See [Of Histograms and Waveforms](https://www.darktable.org/2013/12/of-histograms-and-waveforms/) for more on darktable's waveform scope.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "rgb parade"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "![histogram-parade](./histogram/histogram-parade.png#w33)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "This shows the same data as the waveform, but with the red, green, and blue channels presented side-by-side. When in waveform mode, clicking the second-to-leftmost button on the panel toggles between waveform (overlaid) and RGB parade rendering of the data.  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The RGB parade can be useful for matching the intensities of the red, green, and blue channels. It can also help with understanding the differences between and individual qualities of each channel.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "exposure adjustment"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The histogram can be used to directly alter the _exposure_ and _black level_ of the [_exposure_](../../processing-modules/exposure.md) module.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "For the regular histogram, click towards the right hand side of the histogram and then drag right to increase or drag left to decrease the exposure. In a similar manner you can control the black level by clicking and dragging in the left hand side.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "For waveform-style scopes, dragging the upper portion of the histogram up/down will increase/decrease exposure. Dragging the lower portion up/down will increase/decrease the black level.  \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Scrolling in the appropriate area -- rather than dragging -- will also adjust exposure and black point. Double-click in the histogram to reset the exposure module's parameters to their defaults.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "histogram profile"
msgstr "профіль гістограми"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The image data is converted to the _histogram profile_ before the histogram is calculated. You can choose this profile by right-clicking on the [soft-proof](../darkroom/soft-proof.md) or [gamut check](../darkroom/gamut.md) icons in the bottom panel and then selecting the profile of interest.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/histogram.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "As the histogram runs at the end of the preview pixelpipe, it receives data in display color space. If you are using a display color space which is not \"well behaved\" (this is common for a device profile), then colors which are outside of the gamut of the display profile may be clipped or distorted.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/metadata-editor.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "metadata editor"
msgstr "редактор метаданих"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/metadata-editor.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Edit the metadata (title, description, creator, publisher, rights etc.) of selected images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/metadata-editor.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"metadata entry fields\n"
": A separate field is displayed for each metadata item. Hold Ctrl while scrolling with your mouse to increase the height of a field. Press Ctrl+Enter to insert a new line. Press Enter to apply any text entered in the current metadata field to the selected images. Double-click on a field's label to delete the contents of that field.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/metadata-editor.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"apply\n"
": Apply new settings, from the metadata entry fields, to the selected images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/metadata-editor.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"reset button\n"
": Delete existing metadata from the selected images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/metadata-editor.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The “preferences…” option in the presets menu brings up a dialog where you can configure how metadata is handled within darktable. For each metadata item, two check boxes allow you to restrict how metadata is handled:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/metadata-editor.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"visible \n"
": Show or hide this metadata field. Hidden fields will not be displayed anywhere in darktable and will not be included in exported images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/metadata-editor.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"private\n"
": Keep this metadata field private. Private fields will be displayed within darktable but will not be included in exported images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/metadata-editor.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Fields with both options are unchecked will be displayed within darktable and included in exported images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/filmstrip.md
#: content/overview/user-interface/filmstrip.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "filmstrip"
msgstr "стрічка знімків"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/filmstrip.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The filmstrip can be used to quickly switch between images in any darktable view. The images shown are the same as displayed in the lighttable view and are defined by the currently-selected collection.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/filmstrip.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "![filmstrip](./filmstrip/filmstrip.png)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/filmstrip.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The filmstrip can be switched on and off using the shortcut Ctrl+F. The height of the filmstrip panel can be changed by clicking and dragging its top border.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/filmstrip.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Quickly navigate through the images in the filmstrip by scrolling with the mouse. In the darkroom you can change the photo currently being processed by clicking on another image in the filmstrip.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/filmstrip.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "In the darkroom, the image currently being processed is selected and highlighted. Use Mouse over to select any other image from the filmstrip (in order to act on it with a keyboard shortcut) without changing the image being processed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/filmstrip.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "If you wish to select multiple images in the filmstrip, use Alt+click to select the first image and then Ctrl+click to add to or remove images from the selection or Shift+click select a range of images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/filmstrip.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The following shortcuts are available to select images in the filmstrip or to perform actions on the selected images:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/filmstrip.md
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Ctrl+A         select all images in the filmstrip\n"
"Ctrl+Shift+A   deselect all images\n"
"Ctrl+I         invert the current selection\n"
"\n"
"F1 – F5        toggle color label (red, yellow, green, blue, purple)\n"
"0 – 5          set/change image rating\n"
"R              reject image\n"
"Ctrl+D         duplicate image\n"
"Ctrl+C         copy the full history stack\n"
"Ctrl+V         paste all of the copied history stack\n"
"Alt+Ctrl+C     selectively copy the history stack\n"
"Alt+Ctrl+V     selectively paste from the copied history stack\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/filmstrip.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "See the lighttable's [history stack](../lighttable/history-stack.md) documentation for more details of the copy and paste functionality.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/image-information.md
#, no-wrap
