#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/color-calibration.md
#: content/module-reference/processing-modules/filmic-rgb.md
#: content/slideshow/usage.md content/special-topics/darktable-chart/usage.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "usage"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The following sections describe the operations that can be performed with tags.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "text entry"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The text entry box (shown under the _attach_/_detach_ buttons) has multiple purposes.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "If the _tag dictionary_ list is in _list_ view mode (rather than _tree_ view mode), then typing the first few characters of a tag will bring up a list of suggestions. You can then scroll down with the arrow keys and press Enter to select one of the suggestions. Pressing Enter a second time will attach it to the selected images. You can also edit the name of the tag before pressing Enter -- in this case the tag will be created if it doesn't already exist in the database.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Aside from the auto-completion suggestions, typing some partial text into the text entry box allows you filters the set of tags shown in the _tag dictionary_ window to those whose name or synonym matches the entered text. Press Enter to attach a tag with the entered name to the selected images. If that tag name does not yet exist in the database, it will be created before being attached.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The pop-up menu entry “copy to entry” can be used to copy a selected tag to the text entry box. You can then edit this name and press Enter to create a new tag with that name, making it easy to create multiple tags with similar names.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "**Note:** If you find the auto-completion behaviour annoying, it can be disabled in [preferences > miscellaneous > tags > disable the entry completion](../../../preferences-settings/miscellaneous.md#tags).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "create tag"
msgstr "створити тег"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "There are several ways to create a new tag:\n"
msgstr "Є кілька способів створити новий тег:\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "_Import a text file_. You can import one or more text files in the Lightroom tagging file format. You can also export your tags, edit the exported file, then re-import it. The import function updates existing tags and creates new tags as required. If you change the name of a tag in an imported file, it will be treated as a new tag.\n"
msgstr ""
"_Імпортувати текстовий файл_. Ви можете імпортувати один або кілька "
"текстових файлів у форматі файлів ключових слів Lightroom. Ви також можете "
"експортувати свої теги, відредагувати експортований файл, а потім повторно "
"імпортувати його. Функція імпорту оновлює існуючі теги та створює нові теги "
"за необхідності. Якщо ви зміните назву тегу в імпортованому файлі, він буде "
"розглядатися як новий тег.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "_Import already-tagged images_. This method does not offer any flexibility to change tag names or categories during the import process.\n"
msgstr ""
"_Імпортувати вже позначені зображення_. Цей метод не пропонує гнучкості для "
"зміни імен тегів або категорій під час процесу імпорту.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "_Use the “create tag” sub-menu_. A tag can be created manually, under an existing one (hierarchical) or at the root level.\n"
msgstr ""
"_Використати підменю “створити тег”_. Тег можна створити вручну, під наявним "
"(ієрархічно) або на кореневому рівні.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "_Use the “set as a tag“ sub-menu_. You can set a free node (e.g. ”`places|England`”) as a tag so that it gets implicitly attached to all images tagged with its sub-tags (e.g. ”`places|England|London`”).\n"
msgstr ""
"_Використати підменю “встановити як тег“_. Ви можете встановити вільний "
"вузол (наприклад, ”`places|England`”) як тег, щоб він неявно прикріплювався "
"до всіх зображень, позначених його підтегами (наприклад, "
"”`places|England|London`”).\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "_Type into the text box and press the “new” button_. Hierarchical tags are created using the pipe symbol “`|`” to separate nodes. Note that the entered tag is also attached to any selected images.\n"
msgstr ""
"_Ввести в текстове поле і натиснути кнопку “новий”_. Ієрархічні теги "
"створюються з використанням символу конвеєра “`|`” для розділення вузлів. "
"Зверніть увагу, що введений тег також прикріплюється до будь-яких вибраних "
"зображень.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "A number of tags are automatically generated by darktable when certain actions are undertaken. For example, the tags “`darktable|exported`” and “`darktable|styles|your_style`” can be used to identify images that have been exported and had styles applied, respectively.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "edit/rename tag"
msgstr "редагувати/перейменувати тег"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The _tag dictionary_ can be mainained via the \"edit...\" and \"change path...\" items in the right-click pop-up menu.\n"
msgstr ""
"_Словник тегів_ можна підтримувати за допомогою пунктів \"редагувати...\" та "
"\"змінити шлях...\" у спливному меню, що викликається правою кнопкою миші.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The \"edit...\" operation allows you to change the name of a tag, though you cannot change which node it belongs to (you cannot use the pipe \"|\" symbol in the tag name field). The command is aborted if you try to enter a tag name that already exists. You can set the _private_ and _category_ flags and define _synonyms_ for the tag (see below). These attributes are recorded in the `XMP-dc Subject` and `XMP-lr Hierarchical Subject` metadata entries, respectively. You can control which tags are included in exports by changing settings in the [export](./export.md) module.\n"
msgstr ""
"Операція \"редагувати...\" дозволяє змінити ім'я тегу, хоча ви не можете "
"змінити, якому вузлу він належить (ви не можете використовувати символ \"|\" "
"в полі імені тегу). Команда скасовується, якщо ви намагаєтеся ввести ім'я "
"тегу, яке уже існує. Ви можете встановити прапорці _приватно_ та _категорія_ "
"та визначити _синоніми_ для тегу (див. нижче). Ці атрибути записуються до "
"елементів метаданих `XMP-dc Subject` і ` XMP-lr Hierarchical Subject`, "
"відповідно. Ви можете контролювати, які теги включаються в експортовані "
"зображення, змінюючи налаштування в модулі [експорт](./ export.md).\n"

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "A tag set as “private” is, by default, not exported.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "A tag set as “category” is not exported in `XMP-dc Subject`. However it is exported in `XMP-lr Hierarchical Subject` as this XMP metadata holds the organization of your tags.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "“synonyms” enrich the tag information and are mainly used to assist search engines. For example “juvenile”, “kid” or “youth” can be set as synonyms of “child”. Synonyms can also be used to translate tag names to other languages.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The \"change path...\" operation is only available in the _tree_ view mode, and it shows the number of tagged images which would be impacted by a change to the name of this node. The change path window lets the user change the full path of the node, including the nodes to which it belongs (nodes can be specified using the pipe \"`|`\" symbol). This operation is powerful, but please take care as it can have a significant impact on the metadata of your images. The operation is aborted if the requested change causes a conflict with an existing tag.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "A quick way to organize the tag structure is to drag and drop the nodes. In the _tree_ view mode, you can drag any node and drop it on top of any other node. The first node and its descendants, if any, become descendants of the second node. Dragging over a node automatically opens that node. To place a node at the root level, drag it onto the top of the tagging window. If the requested change causes a conflict with an existing tag, the operation is aborted.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "attach tag"
msgstr "прикріпити тег"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "There are a number of ways to attach an existing tag to a group of selected images:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "click on a tag in the _tag dictionary_ window to select it, then click on the _attach_ button.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "right-click on a tag in the _tag dictionary_ window, to show a pop-up menu, then select the “attach tag” menu item.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "double-click on a tag in the _tag dictionary_ window.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "right-click on a tag shown in the _attached tags_ view to show a pop-up menu. If some of the selected images do not currently have that tag, the \"attach tag to all\" menu item can be used to attach that tag to all the selected images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Type into the text box and press the \"new\" button or the Enter key. This will create the tag if it doesn't already exist, and attach it to the selected images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Press Ctrl+T to open a small text box at the bottom of the central view of the lighttable. Type in the name of a tag and press Enter. The tag will be created if it doesn't exist, and attached to all the selected images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Drag an image or group of images and drop it onto the desired tag.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "When hovering over the images in the ligthtable you can check which tags are attached to the image, either by looking at the _attached tags_ window in the _tagging_ module, or in the _tags_ attribute in the [image information](./image-information.md) module.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "detach tag"
msgstr "від'єднати тег"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "There are several ways to remove a tag from a group of selected images:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "click on a tag in the _attached tag_ window of the _tagging_ module to select the tag, then click on the _detach_ button.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "double-click on a tag in the _attached tag_ window.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "right-click on a tag in the _attached tag_ window, to show a pop-up menu, and select \"detach\".\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "delete tag"
msgstr "видалити тег"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "It is possible to completely remove a tag from all images (whether selected or not) and delete the tag from the database. Because this could impact a large number of images, a warning will be displayed indicating how many images currently have this tag attached. Take this warning seriously as there is no way to undo this action (except by restoring your database and/or XMP sidecar files from a backup). A tag in _tag dictionary_ window can be deleted in the following ways:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "right-click on a tag in the _tag dictionary_ window, to show a pop-up menu, and choose \"delete tag\".\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "right-click on a branch node in the _tag dictionary_ window, to show a pop-up menu, and choose \"delete node\" to delete the selected node together with any child nodes.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "import / export"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The “import” button allows you to choose a text file (which must comply with the Lightroom tag text file format) and import its content. If a tag in the imported file already exists, its properties will be updated, otherwise a new tag will be created.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The “export” button exports your entire tag dictionary into a text file of your choice (Lightroom tag text file format).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/darkroom/navigation.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "navigation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "To see the images bearing a particular tag in the _tag dictionary_ window, right-click on the tag name and choose \"go to tag collection\" in the resulting pop-up menu. This opens a collection in the _collect images_ module showing all images containing this tag. You can also select other tags in the _collect images_ module by double-clicking on the collection for the other tag.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/shared/tagging.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "To return to the collection that was selected before opening a tag collection select the \"go back to work\" item from the pop-up menu. This will allow you to return to the original collection, as long ans you haven't selected any other collections in the meantime.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/find-location.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "find location"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/find-location.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Search for a location on the map. You must be connected to the internet to use this feature.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/find-location.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "To use this module, type in a place name or address, press Enter and a list of results will be shown. Click on one of the resulting items and the map will zoom to that location. An outline covering that location or a pin pointing at the location will be displayed. Drag images from the [filmstrip](../shared/filmstrip.md) at the bottom of the screen to their location on the map. The GPS location will be embedded in the image.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "map settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Select preferred map data from various providers. Some will provide additional layers (satellite view etc.) which you can toggle.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"map source\n"
": Choose the provider to source map information from.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"show OSD\n"
": Choose whether to display the OSD controls on top-left of the center view.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"filtered images\n"
": Select to display only the images from the filmstrip in the center view. De-select to display all images in the current library, where those images have GPS data associated with them. You can also toggle this option by pressing Ctrl+S.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"max images\n"
": Controls the maximum number of displayed thumbnails.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"group size factor\n"
": Increase or decrease the size of the area that causes images to be grouped.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"min images per group\n"
": The minimum number of images that need to be placed in the same position in order to automatically create an image group for them.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/map/map-settings.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"thumbnail display\n"
": Three options are available: image thumbnail, count-only marker (to free space on the map) or nothing at all. When hovering over a count-only marker, the corresponding thumbnail is displayed. A count-only marker behaves the same way as a normal image thumbnail, in terms of color coding, scrolling, drag and drop etc. You can also cycle through these options by pressing Shift+S.\n"
msgstr ""

