msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/select.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Select images in the lighttable according to simple criteria.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/select.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"select all\n"
": Select all images shown in the current lighttable view\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/select.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"select none\n"
": De-select all images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/select.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"invert selection\n"
": Select all images that are not currently selected.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/select.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"select film roll\n"
": Select all images that are in the same film roll as the currently-selected images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/select.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"select untouched\n"
": Select all images that have not yet been developed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "styles"
msgstr "стилі"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Create named styles from selected images' [history stacks](../../../darkroom/pixelpipe/history-stack.md) and apply styles to selected images. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Styles can either be created within this panel or in the [history stack](../darkroom/history-stack.md) module in the darkroom.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "A list of all available styles is displayed at the top of the module. A search field above the list allows you to locate a style by name or description. This module also allows styles to be edited and deleted.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Double-click on a style name to apply that style to all selected images.  A style may also be applied to all selected images by pressing a shortcut key assigned to it (see [preferences > shortcuts](../../../preferences-settings/shortcuts.md)) while in either lighttable or darkroom view.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Remove all styles by clicking on the module reset button.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Please note that styles also include the active state of each module. You can use this to create your own default settings, which you can then activate on-demand. Simply set your desired defaults for each module, disable the module, and save the style.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"create duplicate\n"
": When applying a style to images, tick this box to create a duplicate of each image before applying the chosen style to that duplicate. Disable this option to apply the chosen style directly to the selected images. Beware that in this case any existing history stack is overwritten (depending on the mode -- see below) and cannot be recovered.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mode\n"
": As with the [history stack](./history-stack.md) module, this combobox allows you to either \"append\" the style to the current history stack or to \"overwrite\" the history stack of the target image.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"create\n"
": Create new style(s) using the history stack of the selected image(s). For each selected image a style creation window is shown. You must supply a unique name for each new style and you can also add an optional description. You will be given the option to de-select any history stack items that you don't want to be part of the created style.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": The panel supports a hierarchical view, meaning that you can create categories using the pipe symbol “|” as a separator. For example “print|tone curve +0.5 EV” will create a \"print\" category with a style of \"tone curve +0.5 EV\" below it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"edit\n"
": Select \"edit\" to bring up a dialog which allows you to include or exclude specific items from the stack of an existing style. Check the “duplicate” option if you want to create a new style, instead of overwriting the existing one. In this case you will need to provide a unique name for the new style.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"remove\n"
": Delete the selected style, without any further prompt.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"import\n"
": Import a previously saved style. Styles are stored as XML files with the extension `.dtstyle`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/styles.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"export\n"
": Save the selected style to disk as a `.dtstyle` file. This allows styles to be published and shared with other users.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#: content/preferences-settings/import.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "import"
msgstr "імпорт"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Import images into one or more film rolls.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Images can be imported from the local filesystem or from a connected camera. See [supported file formats](../../../overview/supported-file-formats.md) for more information.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "import from filesystem"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "You can import either a single image or a folder of images from the filesystem by clicking the relevant button. The imported image(s) will be automatically added to a film roll with the same name as the filesystem folder that they are imported from.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Click on “image” or “folder” to open a file selector dialog. Navigate through the filesystem, and select the item(s) to import.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "parameters"
msgstr "параметри"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Click on the \"parameters\" label or the expander button beside it to display the following additional options related to file import.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "All parameters are saved from one session to the next and can be saved as module presets. Press the module reset button to revert all parameters to their default value.\n"
msgstr ""
"Усі параметри зберігаються від одного сеансу до наступного і можуть бути "
"збережені як пресети модуля. Натисніть кнопку скидання параметрів модуля, "
"щоб повернути всі параметри до значень за замовчуванням.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"recursive directory (folder import only)\n"
": Check this option to import images in the selected folder _and all subfolders_. It is recommended that you not use this option to import a large number of images at the same time. The import process causes darktable to generate thumbnails for all of the imported images, but in the end it will only be able to keep the most recent in its cache. It is therefore better to import images in smaller chunks to avoid the performance penalty this imposes.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"ignore JPEG images\n"
": Check this option if there are `JPEG` images in the same folder that you do not want to import. This option is usually used where the camera stores `RAW+JPEG` and you only want to work on the `RAW` files, leaving the `JPEG` images untouched.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"ignore exif rating\n"
": Check this option to ignore any rating stored within the image's Exif data and instead use a hard-coded value (below).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"initial rating\n"
": Initial star rating (from 0 to 5) for all images when importing a film roll (default 1).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"apply metadata\n"
": Check this option to automatically set metadata fields and/or tags at import time (see below).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"metadata\n"
": If the \"apply metadata\" box is checked, a list of the _visible_ metadata fields is presented for completion (see [metadata editor](../shared/metadata-editor.md) for details). Any populated strings are automatically added to the imported images. You can also choose from any presets saved within the metadata editor module.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": Double-click on a label to reset the corresponding field. Double-click on the \"metadata presets\" label to reset all fields.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": When [preferences > storage > write sidecar file for each image](../../../preferences-settings/storage.md#xmp) is unchecked an additional column \"from xmp\" is presented so that you can choose to prevent the import of non-desired metadata from xmp files.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"tags\n"
": If you want to add further tags by default when importing images, you can provide them here as a comma separated list. As with metadata you can also choose from any presets saved within the [tagging](../shared/tagging.md) module.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "**Note:** When importing images from the filesystem, darktable does not create duplicates of your image files in a separate folder structure but processes them in-situ. The import process simply adds details of those images to darktable's database (and creates an XMP sidecar file if applicable) allowing the images to be viewed and developed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "This means that if you delete images from disk after having imported them, darktable cannot access them any more: Importing an image or folder in darktable is not a backup of your filesystem! Moreover, darktable does not watch for changes in the filesystem. Any new images will not be shown until they are explicitly imported.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "import from a connected camera"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "When a camera is detected, it will show up in the device panel automatically. If you hover your mouse over the camera tab label, a tooltip will pop up with information about the camera (model, firmware version etc.). Depending on the capabilities of the camera, the following options may be displayed:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"import from camera\n"
": This will bring up an import dialog, showing any images on camera that can be selected for import into a film roll.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": The base folder for storing imported images and the naming pattern of subfolders and individual images can be set in [preferences > import](../../../preferences-settings/import.md).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"tethered shoot\n"
": Tethering is used to integrate darktable with your camera. When you take images with your camera, they are automatically imported into darktable, so you can review the result of the shoot. You can also setup remote capture jobs, controlling the number of images and time between captures, along with camera settings such as exposure time, aperture etc.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/import.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": If supported by your camera, selecting _tethered shoot_ will take you into the [tethering](../../../tethering/_index.md) view.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/darkroom/history-stack.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "history stack"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Manipulate the history stack of one or more selected images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"selective copy...\n"
": Copy selected parts of the history stack of the selected image. A dialog appears within which you may choose which items from the history stack to include. If more than one image is selected, the history stack is taken from the image that was selected first. Double-click on an item to copy that item only and immediately close the dialog.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"copy\n"
": Copy the complete history stack from the selected image. If more than one image is selected, the history stack is taken from the image that was selected first.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": Information relating to internal display encoding and mask management is considered unsafe to automatically copy to other images and will therefore not be copied when using this button.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": The following modules are excluded from the _copy_ operation:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
": - [_orientation_](../../processing-modules/orientation.md)\n"
": - [_lens correction_](../../processing-modules/lens-correction.md)\n"
": - [_raw black/white point_](../../processing-modules/raw-black-white-point.md)\n"
": - [_rotate pixels_](../../processing-modules/rotate-pixels.md)\n"
": - [_scale pixels_](../../processing-modules/scale-pixels.md)\n"
": - [_white balance_](../../processing-modules/white-balance.md)\n"
": - deprecated modules\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": You can override all of these exclusions by using \"selective paste...\" and choosing which modules to paste to the target image(s).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"compress history\n"
": Generate the shortest history stack that reproduces the current image. If any module appears multiple times in the stack, these occurrences will be _compressed_ into a single step in the history. _Beware, this action can not be undone!_\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"discard history\n"
": Physically delete the history stack of the selected images. _Beware, this action can not be undone!_\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"selective paste...\n"
": Paste selected parts of a previously copied history stack onto all selected images. A dialog appears within which you may choose which items from the source history stack to include.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"paste\n"
": Paste all items of a copied history stack onto all selected images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mode\n"
": This setting defines how the paste actions behave when applied to an image that already has a history stack. In simple terms the “overwrite” mode deletes the previous history stack before pasting, whereas “append” will concatenate the two history stacks together.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": A copied history stack can have multiple entries of the same module (with the same name or different names) and pasting behaves differently for these entries in append and overwrite modes. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": In _append_ mode, for each copied module of the source image, if there is a module in the destination image with the same name it will be replaced. If there is no such module, a new instance will be created. In both cases the pasted instance is placed on top of the history stack. If a particular module appears multiple times in either history stack only the last occurrence of that module will be processed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": In _overwrite_ mode the behavior is the same except that the history of the destination image is deleted before the paste operation commences. The “copy all”/“paste all” actions in this mode will precisely duplicate the entire history stack of the source image onto the destination (including any duplicate occurrences).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Notes\n"
": - Automatic module presets are only added to an image when it is first opened in the darkroom. If you use _overwrite_ mode to paste history stack entries to images that haven't previously been opened in the darkroom then the next time that image is opened in the darkroom, automatic presets will be applied to the image. It may therefore seem as if the “overwrite” mode did not accurately duplicate the existing history stack, but in this case, those automatic modules were added subsequently.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": - The _append_ mode allows you to later reconstruct your pre-existing history stack (because previous history items are retained in the stack of the destination image). However, in “overwrite” mode all previous edits are irrevocably lost.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": - The _mode_ setting is retained when you quit darktable -- if you change it for a one-off copy and paste, make sure to change it back again.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"load sidecar file\n"
": Open a dialog box which allows you to import the history stack from a selected XMP file. This copied history stack can then be pasted onto one or images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": Images that were exported by darktable typically contain the full history stack if the file format supports embedded metadata (see the [export](../shared/export.md) module for details of this feature and its limitations). You can load an exported image as a sidecar file in the same way as you can with an XMP file. This feature allows you to recover all parameter settings if you have accidentally lost or overwritten the XMP file. All you need is the source image, typically a raw, and the exported file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"write sidecar files\n"
": Write XMP sidecar files for all selected images. The filename is generated by appending “.xmp” to the name of the underlying input file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/history-stack.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ": By default darktable generates and updates sidecar files automatically whenever you work on an image and change the history stack. You can disable automatic sidecar file generation in [preferences > storage](../../../preferences-settings/storage.md). This can be useful when you are running multiple versions of darktable (so that edits in each version do not conflict with one another) however, in general, disabling this feature is not recommended.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, no-wrap
msgid "selected images"
msgstr "дії з вибраними зображеннями"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Perform actions on images that have been selected in the lighttable view.\n"
msgstr ""
"Виконує дії над зображеннями, які були вибрані в режимі світлого стола.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "The module controls are spread over two tabs, one for manipulating the image files, and the other for manipulating the metadata related to the images.\n"
msgstr ""
"Елементи керування модулем розподілені по двох вкладках, одна для обробки "
"файлів зображень, а інша для обробки метаданих, пов’язаних із зображеннями.\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "images tab"
msgstr "вкладка \"зображення\""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"remove\n"
": Remove the selected images from the darktable database. Removed images can no longer be viewed or edited within darktable but the image files remain on the filesystem along with any XMP sidecar files. As darktable keeps the XMP files up-to-date with your latest development history, you can later fully restore your work by re-importing the images.\n"
msgstr ""
"видалити\n"
": Видаляє вибрані зображення з бази даних darktable. Видалені зображення "
"більше не можна переглядати або редагувати в darktable, але файли зображень "
"залишаються у файловій системі разом із файлами XMP. Оскільки darktable "
"постійно оновлює файли XMP останньою історією обробки, згодом ви можете "
"повністю відновити свою роботу, повторно імпортувавши зображення.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"delete/trash\n"
": Eliminate the selected images from the darktable database and remove any associated XMP sidecar files. If no duplicates of the selected image remain in the darktable database, the image file itself is also deleted. You can control whether this action irrevocably deletes the images or puts them into your system's trash bin with a configuration item in [preferences > security](../../../preferences-settings/security.md). A second configuration item in the same tab allows you to control whether or not to be prompted before deleting images.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"move\n"
": Physically move selected images (the image file plus all associated XMP sidecar files) to another filesystem folder. If an image with the given filename already exists in the target folder the source image will not be moved.\n"
msgstr ""
"перемістити\n"
": Фізично переміщує вибрані зображення (файл зображення та всі пов’язані з "
"ним файли XMP) до іншої папки файлової системи. Якщо зображення з вказаним "
"іменем файлу вже існує в цільовій папці, джерельне зображення не буде "
"переміщено.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"copy\n"
": Physically copy selected images (the image file plus all associated XMP sidecar file) to another filesystem folder. If an image with the given filename already exists in the target folder it will not be overwritten – instead a new duplicate will be generated with the same history stack as the source image.\n"
msgstr ""
"копіювати\n"
": Фізично копіює вибрані зображення (файл зображення та всі пов'язані з ним "
"файли XMP) до іншої папки файлової системи. Якщо зображення з вказаним "
"іменем файлу вже існує в цільовій папці, воно не буде перезаписано - "
"натомість буде створено новий дублікат із тим самим стеком історії змін, що "
"й джерельне зображення.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"create hdr\n"
": Create a high dynamic range image from the selected images, and store it as a new source file in DNG format. Images need to be properly aligned, which implies that they have been taken on a sturdy tripod. You can also generate HDRs with programs like Luminance HDR, and later import them into darktable for further processing. Note that darktable will only create HDR images from raw files.\n"
msgstr ""
"створити HDR\n"
": Створює зображення із високим динамічним діапазоном (HDR) із вибраних "
"зображень та зберігає його як новий джерельний файл у форматі DNG. "
"Зображення мають бути правильно вирівняні, що означає, що їх потрібно "
"знімати на міцному штативі. Ви також можете генерувати HDR в таких "
"програмах, як Luminance HDR, а згодом імпортувати їх у darktable для "
"подальшої обробки. Зауважте, що darktable створюватиме HDR-зображення лише з "
"raw файлів.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"duplicate\n"
": Create a virtual copy of the selected images within darktable. This allows you to test different edits on the same image, for example. Duplicate images share the same parent input file, but each have their own XMP sidecar file and separate entry in darktable's database.\n"
msgstr ""
"зняти копію\n"
": Створює віртуальну копію вибраних зображень у darktable. Це дозволяє вам, "
"наприклад, тестувати різні редагування одного і того ж зображення. Дублікати "
"зображення мають один і той же батьківський файл, але кожен із них має "
"власний файл XMP та окремий запис у базі даних darktable.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"rotation\n"
": Perform a clockwise or counter-clockwise rotation on the selected images. The third button resets the image rotation to the value stored in the image's Exif data. This feature is directly linked to the [_orientation_](../../../module-reference/processing-modules/orientation.md) processing module -- adjustments made here are automatically converted into a history stack item for that module.\n"
msgstr ""
"обертання\n"
": Виконує обертання за або проти годинникової стрілки на вибраних "
"зображеннях. Третя кнопка скидає обертання зображення до значення, що "
"зберігається в даних Exif зображення. Ця функція безпосередньо пов’язана з "
"модулем обробки [_орієнтація_](../../../module-reference/processing-modules/"
"orientation.md) -- зроблені тут налаштування автоматично перетворюються в "
"елемент стека історії змін для цього модуля.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"copy locally\n"
": This action will create local copies of the selected images on the local drive. These copies will then be used when the original images are not accessible (see [local copies](../../../overview/sidecar-files/local-copies.md)).\n"
msgstr ""
"локальна копія\n"
": Ця дія створить локальні копії вибраних зображень на локальному диску. "
"Потім ці копії будуть використовуватися, коли оригінальні зображення "
"недоступні (див. [локальні копії](../../../overview/sidecar-files/local-"
"copies.md)).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"resync local copy\n"
": This action will synchronize the XMP sidecar of the local copy of each selected image with the copy in external storage, if needed, and will remove the local copies. Note that if a local copy has been modified and the external storage is not accessible the local copy won't be deleted (see [local copies](../../../overview/sidecar-files/local-copies.md)).\n"
msgstr ""
"синхронізувати\n"
": Ця дія синхронізує файл XMP локальної копії кожного вибраного зображення з "
"копією у зовнішньому сховищі, якщо потрібно, та видалить локальні копії. "
"Зверніть увагу, що якщо локальна копія була змінена, а зовнішнє сховище "
"недоступне, локальна копія не буде видалена (див. [локальні копії](../../../"
"overview/sidecar-files/local-copies.md)).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"group\n"
": Create a new group from selected images (see [image grouping](../../../lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md)).\n"
msgstr ""
"згрупувати\n"
": Створює нову групу із вибраних зображень (див. [групування "
"зображень](../../../lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md)).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"ungroup\n"
": Remove selected images from a group (see [image grouping](../../../lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md)).\n"
msgstr ""
"розгрупувати\n"
": Видаляє вибрані зображення з групи (див. [групування зображень](../../../"
"lighttable/digital-asset-management/grouping.md)).\n"

#. type: Title ##
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "metadata tab"
msgstr "вкладка \"метадані\""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"metadata type checkboxes\n"
": Choose which types of metadata (ratings, tags, metadata, colors, geo tags) you want to operate on. \n"
msgstr ""
"прапорці типу метаданих\n"
": Виберіть, з якими типами метаданих (рейтинги, теги, метадані, кольори, "
"геотеги) ви хочете працювати. \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"copy\n"
": Copy the chosen types of metadata from the selected image onto the clipboard. If you have more than one image selected, or no images selected, then this button is unavailable.\n"
msgstr ""
"копіювати\n"
": Копіює вибрані типи метаданих із вибраного зображення в буфер обміну. Якщо "
"у вас вибрано більше одного зображення або жодне зображення не вибрано, ця "
"кнопка недоступна.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"paste\n"
": Paste any metadata in the clipboard onto the selected images.\n"
msgstr ""
"вставити\n"
": Вставляє будь-які метадані в буфері обміну у вибрані зображення.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"clear\n"
": Clear the chosen types of metadata from the selected images.\n"
msgstr ""
"очистити\n"
": Прибирає вибрані типи метаданих із вибраних зображень.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"mode\n"
": When pasting metadata onto images, this option controls whether the metadata on the clipboard should be merged with the existing metadata (_merge_), or should replace it entirely (_overwrite_).\n"
msgstr ""
"режим\n"
": При вставці метаданих у зображення ця опція визначає, чи слід об’єднувати "
"метадані в буфері обміну з наявними метаданими (_об'єднати_), чи замінювати "
"їх повністю (_перезаписати_).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"refresh exif\n"
": Refresh the Exif data from the source file. Warning: this may overwrite some tags that you have subsequently changed in darktable (such as star ratings).\n"
msgstr ""
"оновити exif\n"
": Оновлює дані Exif із джерельного файлу. Попередження: це може перезаписати "
"деякі теги, які ви згодом змінили в darktable (наприклад, рейтинги).\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"monochrome\n"
": Flag the image as monochrome, meaning that it will receive any monochrome-specific workflow treatment that is offered by the processing modules. Refer to the [developing monochrome images](../../../guides-tutorials/monochrome.md) section for more details.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/module-reference/utility-modules/lighttable/selected-image.md
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"color\n"
": Remove the monochrome flag from the image so that it will receive the default workflow treatment that is normally used when developing color photos.\n"
msgstr ""

